OL,3,CNavy veteran remembers being told to
OL,4,C'save who you can' during Boscastle
OL,5,CFloods
OL,7,FHe said the deluge shorted out the
OL,8,Fhelicopter's communications, so the
OL,9,Fpilots and rear crew had to
OL,10,Fcommunicate using hand signals.
OL,12,F"The scene was it was like an action
OL,13,Fmovie. There was beer kegs floating
OL,14,Fdown, cars floating down, I think
OL,15,Fthere was telephone box, people almost
OL,16,Frunning away from the water. You could
OL,17,Fsee parts of buildings missing."
OL,19,FIt was a call from the coastguard
OL,20,Fbefore the comms dropped out fully
OL,21,Fthat really shook the captain.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/9
