OL,3,CNavy veteran remembers being told to
OL,4,C'save who you can' during Boscastle
OL,5,CFloods
OL,7,FFord remembers the children rescued
OL,8,Fcoming up with "big smiles on their
OL,9,Ffaces" while parents "were in deep
OL,10,Fshock" after having to decide which
OL,11,Fchild to send up first.
OL,13,FStrange things were seen during the
OL,14,Frescue operation as an RAF crew put a
OL,15,Fbaby in a rucksack before winching it
OL,16,Fto safety from a car roof.
OL,18,FOne "obscene" memory Lt Cdr Florry
OL,19,FFord has is seeing how the cows
OL,20,Freacted to fish washing up in their
OL,21,Ffield.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
